    "Recall is crucial in situations where missing positive instances is costly.",
    "Mathematically, Recall is defined as:Recall = T P T P + F N. (5)F1 Score: The F1 Score is a harmonic mean of Precision and Recall, providing a balanced measure that considers both false positives and false negatives.",
    "It is particularly useful when there is an uneven class distribution.",
    "The F1 Score reaches its maximum at 1 (perfect precision and recall) and its minimum at 0.",
    "Mathematically, F1 Score is defined as:F1 Score = 2 × (Precision × Recall) Precision + Recall."
